President Trump delivered a speech at the International Association of Chiefs of Police conference in Orlando, Florida, expressing his support and gratitude for law enforcement. He praised the work of law enforcement in keeping America safe and highlighted the progress his administration has made in reducing crime rates. Trump also discussed his administration's efforts to combat the opioid crisis and improve school safety. He emphasized the importance of supporting and protecting law enforcement officers and condemned the vilification of police. Trump also recognized four nominees for the IACP Police Officer of the Year Award and their acts of bravery. He concluded by reaffirming his commitment to always have law enforcement's back.